metadata.description: 6th in series. Dolittle returns from his voyages & sets his house in order. This includes expanding his zoo to include a home for crossbred dogs & a club for rodents. Dolittle's zoo is different from all others because there are no cages; the animals stay there voluntarily and are free to leave whenever they want. The doctor also takes time to solve a mystery with the aid of Kling, the Dog Detective. Various members of the Rat and Mouse Club telling their life stories.
